# Proof & eval tooling

These back the graded challenges in `docs/project_guidelines.md` §7/§10 and the rubric's honesty bar.
**Do not install these dependencies until the owning lane starts** — dep additions (Cargo.lock, a new
`ml/` Python env) are batched into that lane's FREEZE by the supervisor, to avoid front-loading unused
tooling. This rule is the spec for each tool.

## Benchmark harness — challenge 7h (Lane G)
- Add the `criterion` dev-dependency and a **`just bench`** recipe that loads the shared **50,000-card**
  deck and reports **p50, p95, and worst-case** for each action: button-press ack, next-card after
  grade, dashboard first load, dashboard refresh, sync of a normal session. One hand-picked number
  does **not** count (§10).
- Pair with a **synthetic deck generator** (a script/fixture that builds the 50k-card deck) so the
  benchmark and large-scale tests are reproducible.
- Targets to check against: §10 (p95 button <50 ms, next-card <100 ms, dashboard load <1 s, refresh
  <500 ms, sync <5 s).

## Held-out eval + calibration — Friday/Sunday (Lane D)
- A **`uv`-managed `ml/` environment** with `numpy`, `scipy`, `scikit-learn`, `matplotlib`.
- **Memory calibration:** reliability (calibration) chart + **Brier score / log loss** on held-out
  reviews (when it says 80%, recall ≈ 80%).
- **Performance:** accuracy on held-out exam-style questions.
- **Pre-register the cutoff** before looking at results; AI outputs must trace to a named source and
  **beat a simple baseline** (keyword/vector search).

## Leakage check — challenge 7e (Lane D)
- A script that scans training data for any held-out test item or a near-duplicate, and reports clean.
- Leaked test data **zeroes** that score (rubric §11) — this gate is mandatory before any eval number
  is reported.

## Crash / offline tests — challenge 7g (Lane G/F)
- A script that **kills a review mid-session 20×** in a row and asserts **`pragma integrity_check ==
  ok`** afterward (zero corrupted collections, both platforms).
- An offline test: AI features turn off cleanly while both apps keep working and still give a score.

## AI-off invariant
Everything above must hold with **AI switched off** — the MVP and all core scores run without model
calls (see PRD "Out of Scope for MVP").
